{"name": "ayonix", "metadata": {"name": "ayonix", "version": "0.1.2", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/Silicon27/call", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["requests"], "summary": "A modern CLI program for API testing", "upload_time": 1734790083}, "documentation": ["# Ayonix\n\nA CLI program for API testing.\n\n## Features\n\n- Send HTTP requests to specified URLs\n- Supports GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, and other HTTP methods\n- Include headers and data in requests\n- Measure and display response time\n- Calculate average response time over multiple requests\n- Display response status code, headers, and content\n\n## Installation\n\nYou can install the package using `pip`:\n```bash\npip install ayonix\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nThe usage name for Ayonix is `call`:\n```bash\ncall \"https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts\" --method POST -H '{\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"}' -d '{\"title\": \"foo\", \"body\": \"bar\", \"userId\": 1}'\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "src", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "src.main", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "src.main.call_api", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "url", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "method", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "headers", "type": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "data", "type": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "only_content", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--